cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry (decomposition of coverings), which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem is also related to discrete structures (covering and partitioning), which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The use of a constant alpha in the proof suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The motivation for the problem (sensor network) suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the problem involves monitoring a region, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may also be a relevant sub-category.
